column169: Description Of Events

Package was found with wet outer contents. Upon investigation, package was found to have 4 inner bottles. One bottle had a loose lid causing internal leakage. Package was placed into a hazmat bag, and then into a salvage drum.

Dayton Freight personnel observed approximately three (3) gallons of material released from four (4) 1-gallon plastic jugs. The released material impacted the trailer floor and Dayton Freight personnel deployed granular absorbents to the impacted area and gathered the spent material. The recovered material was containerized into one (1) 15-gallon poly drum and the damaged plastic jugs were placed into one (1) additional 15-gallon poly drum. The generated waste was staged onsite at the terminal in a secure location. The generated waste will remain onsite for Dayton Freight’s contracted hazardous waste vendor to coordinate disposal.

XPO-LOGISTICS contacted ERTS regarding five torn 55lb bags of Caustic Soda Beads. The reason for the incident is improper loading as the bags were torn by the trailer wall. This resulted in an estimated release of 250lbs of  product onto the wooden trailer floor in a 15’x4’ area. A Contractor was called to overpack the damaged bags,  cut-up the impacted tote, neutralize the trailer floor using a Vinegar Solution, and containerized the ripped  shrink wrap. One 55-gallon DF was generated for waste disposal. The remaining product was repalletized and  will ship on to the Consignee. No storm-drains, waterways or soil were impacted by this incident.
